What:
Quick one: I think we should get validation on WAZP processes. The questions are: 

1) Can they get to the same results as Wanhua but on a different printer (Shane wants to print on EOS)
2) How does their post processing perform in lab tests (do we have an answer on their surface finishing yet? have you received the parts)?

In order to do so I propose we get 2 things underway…
1) Have Wanhua print 2 further pairs of shoes and send them to WAZP for post processing
2) Send WAZP a few kg of Wanhua TPU to find out if they can achieve the same results (this may take WAZP a little longer to do the fine tuning)
3) Get print results wear tested and validated by Jean Paul Sartre.
